  "prompt": "What is the procedure for 48 days Lord Murugan fasting?",
  "response": "The 48-day Lord Murugan fasting, also known as Skanda Sashti Vratam, is a significant observance primarily followed by devotees in South India, especially in Tamil Nadu. Here's a general procedure:\n\n1. Preparation:\n- Start on a specific date (usually after Diwali)\n- Take a holy bath daily\n- Wear clean, preferably saffron or yellow clothes\n- Maintain physical and mental purity\n\n2. Daily Routine:\n- Wake up early (around 4-5 AM)\n- Take a bath\n- Wear fresh clothes\n- Perform pooja to Lord Murugan\n- Chant Murugan mantras\n- Offer prayers and special offerings\n\n3. Dietary Guidelines:\n- Follow a strict vegetarian diet\n- Avoid non-vegetarian food\n- Minimize salt and spices\n- Some devotees practice partial fasting\n- Consume fruits, milk, and simple foods\n- Avoid alcohol and tobacco\n\n4. Spiritual Practices:\n- Regular temple visits\n- Recite Skanda Sashti Kavacham\n- Meditate\n- Perform devotional singing\n- Practice celibacy\n\n5. Final Day:\n- Special prayers and celebrations\n- Break the fast with traditional offerings\n\nNote: Specific practices may vary by region and individual traditions.",
